# Part 2 — Describe a child you know who likes drawing very much

One child who immediately comes to mind is my cousin’s daughter, Lily, who is around eight years old now. I’ve known her since she was born because our families are quite close, and we often get together during holidays and family dinners. Ever since she was little, she has shown a strong interest in drawing, and honestly, I think she’s far more creative than many adults.

In terms of personality, she’s a very quiet and imaginative child. Unlike some kids who enjoy running around all day, she can sit at a desk for hours just drawing cartoons, animals, or imaginary cities. She’s also extremely observant. For example, when we go to parks or museums, she pays attention to tiny details like the shape of leaves, the color of the sky, or people’s facial expressions, and later she includes those details in her drawings.

As for how often she draws, I would say almost every day. According to her mother, she usually finishes her homework quickly so she can spend time sketching. Sometimes she even watches online tutorials to learn how to shade pictures or design comic characters. Last year, she won a small art competition at school, which made her even more passionate about drawing.

I think the reason she enjoys drawing so much is that it allows her to express herself freely. Children sometimes find it difficult to explain their feelings through words, but art gives them another way to communicate. Also, drawing gives her a sense of achievement because every time she completes a picture, people praise her creativity and effort. Personally, I really admire her passion because nowadays many children spend most of their time on phones or video games, while she has developed such a meaningful and artistic hobby.

### 中文翻译：

我立刻想到的一个孩子是我表姐的女儿 Lily，她现在大概八岁左右。我从她出生就认识她，因为我们两家关系非常亲近，经常会在节假日或者家庭聚会时见面。从她很小的时候开始，她就对画画表现出浓厚兴趣。说实话，我觉得她比很多成年人都更有创造力。

性格方面，她是一个很安静、很有想象力的孩子。不像一些喜欢整天跑来跑去的小孩，她可以安静地坐在桌前几个小时画卡通人物、动物或者想象中的城市。而且她观察力特别强。比如我们去公园或者博物馆时，她会注意树叶的形状、天空的颜色，甚至是人们的表情，之后她还会把这些细节画进作品里。

至于她画画的频率，我觉得几乎是每天都画。她妈妈说她通常会很快写完作业，然后花时间画画。有时候她还会看网上教程，学习怎么给画面上阴影或者设计漫画角色。去年她还在学校的小型绘画比赛中获奖，这让她对画画更加热爱了。

我觉得她之所以这么喜欢画画，是因为画画能让她自由表达自己。孩子有时候很难用语言准确表达感受，而艺术给了他们另一种沟通方式。另外，画画还能给她成就感，因为每次完成作品后，别人都会夸奖她的创造力和努力。我个人非常欣赏她的热情，因为现在很多孩子大部分时间都花在手机和电子游戏上，而她却培养了这样一个有意义、富有艺术性的爱好。

